                                                          </div>
                                                                                            <p class="word-copy-lh-mb" style="line-height:normal;"><strong>Sanya Osha</strong> is the author of several books, including&nbsp;<em>Postethnophilosophy</em> (2011),&nbsp;<em>Dust, Spittle and Wind</em> (2011),&nbsp;<em>An Underground Colony of Summer Bees</em> (2012), and&nbsp;<em>Ken Saro-Wiwa’s Shadow</em> (expanded ed., 2021), among other publications. A Cape Town, South Africa–based scholar, he is a research associate at ZMO Berlin and a fellow of the African Studies Centre in Leiden.</p>
